  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f6a24499ac4184dc79a002cdfe2c07a7, type: 3}
  m_Name: PeleEndDialogue
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  isConversation: 1
  speakerName:
  - Pele
  - You
  - Pele
  - You
  - Pele
  - You
  - Pele
  - Pele
  paragraphs:
  - You've returned everything.
  - Dear God, woman! How do you keep appearing like that? Yes, I've put it all back.
    Every last piece. Are you satisfied now?
  - None of this was my doing. The forest itself is what kept you here. Do you understand
    why?
  - I was trapped here until I returned everything, but I still don't understand
    how or why. I must admit though, I didn't expect returning a few artifacts to
    have such a profound effect on the atmosphere.
  - These are not mere artifacts. They are vessels of mana, connections between our
    world and the realm of spirits. When you took them, you severed those connections.
    The forest mourned.
  - I'm beginning to understand that my academic perspective was... insufficient.
    There are forces at work here that cannot be catalogued or studied in a laboratory.
    But how am I to leave this place?
  - The forest kept you here to learn. Now that the lesson is complete...
  - ...it will release you.
